summary: This document is a July 15, 2021 trial preparation memo for an AUSA (Assistant United States Attorney). It outlines evidence a witness can authenticate related to the October 20, 2005 search of 358 El Brillo Way, including a map, video, photographs, property receipts, and a green massage table. It notes the chain of custody from the Palm Beach Police Department to the FBI.

events.title: Search of 358 El Brillo Way
events.description: Law enforcement conducted a search of the property at 358 El Brillo Way. Evidence seized included a green massage table, photographs, and video of the search.

events.title: Evidence Transfer to FBI
events.description: All evidence seized from the October 20, 2005 search of 358 El Brillo Way was transferred from the Palm Beach Police Department to an FBI agent.

locations: PBPD office (Palm Beach Police Department office)
keyFacts: A search warrant was executed at 358 El Brillo Way on October 20, 2005.
A green massage table was seized during the search of 358 El Brillo Way.
Evidence from the search was initially stored in a vault at the Palm Beach Police Department office.
The evidence was transferred from the Palm Beach Police Department to the FBI on or about August 28, 2006.
The document is a trial preparation memo for an AUSA, indicating ongoing legal proceedings related to the 2005 search.
